<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-30T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-30T18:00:00-05:00" n="185" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00113 E.W./9–1644: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gallman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-30T19:00:00-04:00">October
                                    30, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>9052. Department’s 6485 of August 16. In view of absence of any official
                            British or Russian response to our proposal and questions posed in 4037
                            from Moscow<note n="33" xml:id="d185fn33">Dated October 22, <ref target="#pg_365">p. 365</ref>.</note> (repeated to London from
                            Moscow as 232, October 22) please defer further action along lines of
                            Department’s 8689 of October 19 until decisions have been reached here
                            on these questions.</p>
                        <p>Similar instructions have been sent to Moscow.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>